str2: Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

str2: Many times, often, frequently. Multiplicative adverb from polus; many times, i.e. Frequently.
Just as, as, even as. From hos and per; just as, i.e. Exactly like.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
High priest, chief priest. From arche and hiereus; the high-priest; by extension a chief priest.

str2: To go in, come in, enter. From eis and erchomai; to enter.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Set apart by (or for) God, holy, sacred. From hagos; sacred.
A primary particle; down, in varied relations (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined).
A year, cycle of time. Prolongation from a primary enos; a year.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Blood, literally, figuratively or specially; by implication, bloodshed, also kindred.
From allos; another's, i.e. Not one's own; by extension foreign, not akin, hostile.
